<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>advanced_react_patterns_compound_components — learning.log</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;600&display=swap"
          rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- Same style as index.html -->
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg: #0a0a0a;
            --bg-elevated: #1a1a1a;
            --text: #e0e0e0;
            --text-dim: #808080;
            --green: #00ff00;
            --cyan: #00ffff;
            --yellow: #ffff00;
            --red: #ff0000;
            --border: #333333;
        }

        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
            background: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.6;
            font-size: 14px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        body::before {
            content: '';
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            background: repeating-linear-gradient(
                    0deg,
                    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15),
                    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15) 1px,
                    transparent 1px,
                    transparent 2px
            );
            pointer-events: none;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .terminal {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: var(--bg-elevated);
            border: 2px solid var(--border);
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .terminal-header {
            background: var(--bg);
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .terminal-button {
            width: 12px;
            height: 12px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        .terminal-button.red {
            background: var(--red);
        }

        .terminal-button.yellow {
            background: var(--yellow);
        }

        .terminal-button.green {
            background: var(--green);
        }

        .terminal-title {
            flex: 1;
            text-align: center;
            color: var(--text-dim);
            font-size: 12px;
        }

        .terminal-body {
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .prompt {
            color: var(--green);
        }

        .command {
            color: var(--cyan);
        }

        .cursor {
            display: inline-block;
            width: 8px;
            height: 16px;
            background: var(--green);
            animation: blink 1s infinite;
        }

        @keyframes blink {
            0%, 50% {
                opacity: 1;
            }
            51%, 100% {
                opacity: 0;
            }
        }

        header {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border);
        }

        .back-link {
            color: var(--yellow);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 13px;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        .back-link:hover {
            color: var(--cyan);
        }

        .back-link::before {
            content: '< ';
            color: var(--green);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 18px;
            color: var(--cyan);
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        h1::before {
            content: '$ cat ';
            color: var(--green);
        }

        .meta {
            color: var(--text-dim);
            font-size: 12px;
            margin: 12px 0 20px 0;
        }

        .meta span {
            margin-right: 20px;
        }

        .meta strong {
            color: var(--yellow);
        }

        .content {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        .content h2, .content h3 {
            color: var(--cyan);
            margin: 2em 0 0.8em 0;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .content h2::before {
            content: '## ';
            color: var(--yellow);
        }

        .content h3::before {
            content: '### ';
            color: var(--text-dim);
        }

        .content p {
            margin-bottom: 1.2em;
        }

        .content code {
            background: #111;
            padding: 2px 6px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            color: var(--cyan);
            font-family: inherit;
        }

        .content pre {
            background: #111;
            padding: 14px;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--green);
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 1.4em 0;
            font-size: 13px;
        }

        .content ul, .content ol {
            margin: 1em 0 1em 1.8em;
        }

        .content li {
            margin-bottom: 0.6em;
        }

        .content blockquote {
            border-left: 3px solid var(--yellow);
            padding-left: 14px;
            color: var(--text-dim);
            font-style: italic;
            margin: 1.5em 0;
        }

        .tags {
            margin-top: 2.5em;
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .tag {
            color: var(--text-dim);
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 3px 9px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        .tag::before {
            content: '#';
            color: var(--green);
            margin-right: 3px;
        }

        footer {
            margin-top: 60px;
            padding-top: 20px;
            border-top: 1px dashed var(--border);
            text-align: center;
            color: var(--text-dim);
            font-size: 11px;
        }

        .command-line {
            margin: 20px 0;
            color: var(--text-dim);
            font-size: 12px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            body {
                padding: 12px;
                font-size: 13px;
            }

            .terminal {
                border-width: 1px;
            }

            .terminal-body {
                padding: 16px;
            }

            .content {
                font-size: 13px;
            }

            pre {
                font-size: 12px;
                padding: 12px;
            }
        }

        .ascii-art {
            color: var(--green);
            font-size: 10px;
            line-height: 1.2;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            white-space: pre;
            font-family: monospace;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="terminal">
    <div class="terminal-header">
        <div class="terminal-button red"></div>
        <div class="terminal-button yellow"></div>
        <div class="terminal-button green"></div>
        <div class="terminal-title">
            user@localhost:~/learning/advanced_react_patterns_compound_components.md
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ascii-art">
        {{ ascii_title }}
    </div>
    <div class="terminal-body">
        <header>
            <a href="index.html" class="back-link">back to learning.log</a>
            <h1>advanced_react_patterns_compound_components</h1>
            <div class="meta">
                <span><strong>DATE:</strong> {{ date }}</span>
                <span><strong>CATEGORY:</strong> {{  categories }}</span>
{#                <span><strong>DURATION:</strong> ~45 min read</span>#}
            </div>
            <div class="command-line">
                <span class="prompt">user@localhost</span>:<span
                    class="command">~/learning</span>$ cat
                advanced_react_patterns_compound_components.md
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="content">
            <h2>Core Idea</h2>
            <p> {{ description }}</p>

            <h2>Classic (bad) example – prop drilling</h2>
            <pre><code>&lt;Select value={selected} onChange={setSelected}&gt;
  &lt;Option value="apple"&gt;Apple&lt;/Option&gt;
  &lt;Option value="banana"&gt;Banana&lt;/Option&gt;
  &lt;Option value="orange"&gt;Orange&lt;/Option&gt;
&lt;/Select&gt;</code></pre>

            <h2>Compound version</h2>
            <pre><code>&lt;Select&gt;
  &lt;Select.Option value="apple"&gt;Apple&lt;/Select.Option&gt;
  &lt;Select.Option value="banana"&gt;Banana&lt;/Select.Option&gt;
  &lt;Select.Option value="orange"&gt;Orange&lt;/Select.Option&gt;
&lt;/Select&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>Behind the scenes <code>Select</code> provides context and <code>Select.Option</code>
                consumes it.</p>

            <h2>Implementation (Context + Compound)</h2>


            <h2>Benefits observed</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>No prop drilling</li>
                <li>Very clean public API</li>
                <li>Easy to compose / extend</li>
                <li>Natural feeling DX (developer experience)</li>
                <li>Works well with render props & hooks too</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Real-world places seen</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Headless UI (Radix, Reach, Headless UI v2)</li>
                <li>React Aria Components</li>
                <li>Many design system select / tabs / accordion / dialog
                    implementations
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Trade-offs / gotchas</h2>
            <blockquote>
                Harder to reason about for new team members — implicit magic is
                still magic.
            </blockquote>
            <p>→ Good naming + documentation helps a lot.</p>

            <blockquote>
                Slightly more complex internal implementation (context +
                composition).
            </blockquote>

            <h2>Takeaway (2026 perspective)</h2>
            <p>Compound components + context still one of the cleanest ways to
                build flexible, composable UI primitives in 2026 — especially
                when combined with <strong>React Server Components</strong> and
                <strong>use()</strong> hook patterns that are becoming more
                common.</p>

            <div class="tags">
                <span class="tag">react</span>
                <span class="tag">design_patterns</span>
                <span class="tag">frontend</span>
                <span class="tag">component_composition</span>
                <span class="tag">context</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <footer>
            <div class="command-line">
                <span class="prompt">user@localhost</span>:<span
                    style="color:#808080;">~/learning</span>$ <span
                    class="cursor"></span>
            </div>
            <p style="margin-top:12px;">EOF | continuously learning | 2026</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>